Journal of Neurology, Neurosurgery & PsychiatryJNNP EPFL 
属于神经义肢neuroprosthetics： prosthesis embodiment is to design artificial limbs that are experienced (‘embodied’) like real limb
现状：bionic limbs没有连续的多感觉反馈
方法：结合外围的神经触觉刺激诱导missing手的触觉感peripheral neurotactile stimulation—inducing tactile sensation on the missing limb
         vr中假手发光immersive digital technology—providing visual illumination of the prosthetic han
目标：检测这种视触觉组合VTNSvisuo-tactile neural stimulation，能不能诱发较强的本体反应、减小对假肢的混乱感觉（假肢常被感知是缩小版）
被试：2人。transradial left forearm chronic amputees：问题：upper limb telescoping
with transverse intrafascicular multichannel electrodes 横向 束内多通道电极TIMEs
触觉：Patients were implanted with transverse intrafascicular multichannel electrodes (TIMEs), 
which induced the sensation of a vibration in a circumscribed skin region of the finger 2 
via 内侧神经刺激medial nerve stimulation in patient 1 (online supplementary figure 1A) 
and in a skin region of finger 5 via 尺骨神经刺激ulnar nerve stimulation in patient 2 (online supplementary figure 1B and material 1)
视觉：和触觉同步，在假肢有触觉的位置自动产生视觉明亮
对照组:视触觉不同步有1.5~2.5s延迟
度量标准:questionnaire& body landmark task:  patients indicated the perceived position of different parts of the phantom limb by moving a ruler in absence of visual stimulation 


